  "summary": "Malicious npm package: trojan main entry exfiltrates console output to attacker Telegram/Firebase",
  "details": "The package advertises itself as a fetch wrapper but its declared main (index.js) silently replaces the global `console` with a Proxy that exfiltrates every logged value to an attacker-controlled Telegram bot and a Firebase realtime database,. Hardcoded Telegram bot token and imgbb API key are shipped in the require-time-reachable module, matching the hardcoded-provider-credentials block pattern. The legitimate-looking zlFetch code in src/ and dist/ is never reached because package.json's main points at the exfiltration file — a deliberate trojan/masquerade. Static YARA rules independently confirmed Telegram sendMessage exfiltration in index.js and src/6cc.js (a static pattern match). Multiple independent critical signals (two exfiltration channels + hardcoded creds + trojan masquerade) leave no ambiguity.",
